It's so itchy.
Is it because I didn't wash my hair?

45
00:03:24,064 --> 00:03:25,098
Hey.

46
00:03:26,032 --> 00:03:28,524
Let's try not meet in the mornings.

47
00:03:29,569 --> 00:03:30,637
Why?

48
00:03:31,938 --> 00:03:34,776
I just prefer seeing you in the evening.

49
00:03:35,150 --> 00:03:36,196
Silly.

50
00:03:38,278 --> 00:03:40,506
Why do you want to see me in the evenings?

51
00:03:49,823 --> 00:03:50,824
Who is it that?

52
00:03:51,124 --> 00:03:52,370
Why are you ignoring the call?

53
00:03:52,818 --> 00:03:54,282
It's a telemarketer.

54
00:03:56,763 --> 00:03:58,771
Why are you being so nosy?

55
00:03:59,660 --> 00:04:01,195
Did she call you?

56
00:04:01,287 --> 00:04:03,228
She didn't, so eat up.

57
00:04:03,374 --> 00:04:05,560
I told her clearly back then...

58
00:04:05,651 --> 00:04:08,815
...that I'd kill her if she
showed up around you again.

59
00:04:09,276 --> 00:04:12,196
Wait and see if I'm true to my words.

60
00:04:19,786 --> 00:04:23,019
Hello, how have you been?

61
00:04:23,401 --> 00:04:25,758
I miss everyone.

62
00:04:26,624 --> 00:04:27,582
Yes.

63
00:04:28,196 --> 00:04:30,871
Do you know what she's doing now?

64
00:04:30,962 --> 00:04:33,276
I think her name was Aera.

65
00:04:35,075 --> 00:04:37,712
Yes, that's right, Choi Aera.

66
00:04:39,024 --> 00:04:40,987
No, we weren't close.

67
00:04:41,122 --> 00:04:43,857
I thought she'd be in my field by now.

68
00:04:44,351 --> 00:04:46,804
What? At a department store?

69
00:04:48,915 --> 00:04:49,977
So...

70
00:04:50,177 --> 00:04:54,264
...you got back from changing
and found this here?

71
00:04:56,034 --> 00:04:57,909
What could it be?

72
00:04:58,109 --> 00:04:59,825
Who'd leave this here?

73
00:05:00,931 --> 00:05:02,917
Did a terrorist leave it?

74
00:05:03,879 --> 00:05:05,774
What do you think?

75
00:05:05,974 --> 00:05:07,628
Should I open it?

76
00:05:09,388 --> 00:05:10,388
Don't.

77
00:05:11,199 --> 00:05:13,820
Why not? Do you have a bad feeling too?

78
00:05:14,824 --> 00:05:17,376
This was packed by an expert.

79
00:05:17,576 --> 00:05:20,521
It looks like just
the packaging cost 20,000 won.

80
00:05:20,676 --> 00:05:23,691
What if the owner comes back
and demands compensation?

81
00:05:23,994 --> 00:05:25,678
Let's leave it then.

82
00:05:26,763 --> 00:05:30,239
I'll put out a broadcast
and ask if someone lost it.

83
00:05:32,002 --> 00:05:35,189
Let's leave it here for now.

84
00:05:36,633 --> 00:05:37,681
Here?

85
00:05:38,434 --> 00:05:40,708
Reject Call

86
00:05:51,278 --> 00:05:54,476
Answer your phone,
or I'll go to your house.

87
00:06:18,782 --> 00:06:20,155
One gimbap, please.

88
00:06:28,318 --> 00:06:29,420
Hey, Aera.

89
00:06:39,416 --> 00:06:42,647
Park Hyeran is eating
a 1,000 won gimbap right now.

90
00:06:42,847 --> 00:06:44,077
Is this reality?

91
00:06:47,055 --> 00:06:49,043
Aren't you going to eat?

92
00:06:49,243 --> 00:06:50,543
I'm dieting.

93
00:06:50,743 --> 00:06:52,245
Then why are you here?

94
00:06:52,445 --> 00:06:54,257
I bought it for someone.

95
00:06:54,674 --> 00:06:57,586
But coincidentally, I saw you here.

96
00:06:57,870 --> 00:06:59,083
It's good to see you.

97
00:07:01,660 --> 00:07:02,874
Was it really a coincidence?

98
00:07:03,529 --> 00:07:06,258
Hyeran, a conglomerate
family's daughter-in-law,

99
00:07:06,349 --> 00:07:08,851
happened to show up
at a dollar gimbap place...

100
00:07:09,051 --> 00:07:11,804
...near my workplace during my lunch break.

101
00:07:12,028 --> 00:07:13,340
That's a coincidence?

102
00:07:14,228 --> 00:07:16,211
Nothing happens by coincidence with you.

103
00:07:16,411 --> 00:07:19,686
Since we met anyway,
give me Dongman's number.

104
00:07:19,886 --> 00:07:21,607
Or his address.

105
00:07:22,481 --> 00:07:24,687
Why do you care?

106
00:07:25,237 --> 00:07:27,652
I have no reason to tell you.

107
00:07:27,848 --> 00:07:29,265
You know his number, right?

108
00:07:30,225 --> 00:07:31,217
No, I don't.

109
00:07:32,648 --> 00:07:33,647
You don't?

110
00:07:35,226 --> 00:07:36,666
We don't keep in touch anymore,

111
00:07:36,770 --> 00:07:38,562
ever since he got married and moved away.

112
00:07:38,995 --> 00:07:41,313
It felt strange calling a married man.

113
00:07:41,479 --> 00:07:43,096
That's proper etiquette.

114
00:07:43,187 --> 00:07:45,663
I see. Is that right?

115
00:07:45,754 --> 00:07:47,496
Etiquette.

116
00:07:48,071 --> 00:07:49,989
You know what that is, don't you?

117
00:08:01,925 --> 00:08:03,423
Leave Dongman alone.

118
00:08:03,798 --> 00:08:05,957
Don't think about him
and stay away from him.

119
00:08:06,060 --> 00:08:09,440
You have not changed at all.

120
00:08:11,845 --> 00:08:14,106
This is so heavy.

121
00:08:14,920 --> 00:08:15,814
Gosh.

122
00:08:17,567 --> 00:08:20,999
If you exterminate the mites,

123
00:08:21,199 --> 00:08:23,661
I'll work on the bidet and filter...

124
00:08:24,794 --> 00:08:25,660
Me?

125
00:08:26,384 --> 00:08:28,292
You want me to do the fumigation?

126
00:08:29,021 --> 00:08:30,789
That's your part.

127
00:08:31,193 --> 00:08:33,185
We need to do our
own parts to finish quickly.

128
00:08:33,276 --> 00:08:35,105
Do you like dividing up the duties?

129
00:08:35,780 --> 00:08:38,202
But you know, in Korea,

130
00:08:38,293 --> 00:08:41,950
we follow hierarchy. You know, seniority.

131
00:08:42,723 --> 00:08:45,380
So are you telling me...

132
00:08:46,192 --> 00:08:49,185
...to do everything myself?

133
00:08:49,276 --> 00:08:50,459
Why are you asking?

134
00:08:51,307 --> 00:08:54,457
You sound like you
haven't served in the military.

135
00:08:56,209 --> 00:08:57,878
Does this work? My bad. Sorry.

136
00:08:57,969 --> 00:08:59,603
My gosh.

137
00:09:00,477 --> 00:09:02,667
They're so stingy.

138
00:09:02,829 --> 00:09:04,699
Why are they making us eat the cherries?

139
00:09:04,858 --> 00:09:08,234
I like it. It's like break time.

140
00:09:08,427 --> 00:09:10,716
-It tastes good.
-We need to shoot people...

141
00:09:10,807 --> 00:09:13,121
...eating the cherries,
so act like they taste good.

142
00:09:13,212 --> 00:09:14,219
-Okay.
-Okay.

143
00:09:14,310 --> 00:09:18,779
Also, mix it with the salad
and yogurt too.

144
00:09:18,870 --> 00:09:20,612
-Yes, sir.
-Enjoy.

145
00:09:20,703 --> 00:09:22,020
-Okay.
-Okay.

146
00:09:22,339 --> 00:09:23,989
I said not the yogurt.

147
00:09:35,646 --> 00:09:37,022
Smile more, please.

148
00:09:40,963 --> 00:09:42,013
Yogurt!

149
00:09:54,137 --> 00:09:56,223
What are they saying?
Why are they smiling?

150
00:09:58,486 --> 00:10:00,533
"Me too?" What does that mean?

151
00:10:01,258 --> 00:10:02,203
Me too.

152
00:10:08,951 --> 00:10:09,982
What's wrong with her?

153
00:10:11,106 --> 00:10:12,631
-Oh no.
-Are you okay?

154
00:10:12,855 --> 00:10:13,828
Stop.

155
00:10:14,028 --> 00:10:16,791
Someone help! I think she's choking!

156
00:10:25,742 --> 00:10:26,655
Step aside.

157
00:11:19,352 --> 00:11:21,007
Was he big and tall?

158
00:11:21,095 --> 00:11:22,193
There's nobody like you.

159
00:11:22,284 --> 00:11:23,427
Can you do it, Dongman?

160
00:11:23,547 --> 00:11:24,705
Anywhere at all.

161
00:11:24,796 --> 00:11:27,669
Why does Seolhui get to play Snow White?

162
00:11:28,870 --> 00:11:30,794
Because she is.

163
00:11:30,994 --> 00:11:34,380
-Got a problem with that?
-You're just a tree.

164
00:11:34,471 --> 00:11:38,164
I'm a special tree.

165
00:11:39,190 --> 00:11:42,769
You just have to kiss Seolhui now.

166
00:11:42,860 --> 00:11:44,475
What?

167
00:12:03,485 --> 00:12:06,448
I don't want to.

168
00:12:10,416 --> 00:12:11,773
What's wrong with you?

169
00:12:12,172 --> 00:12:14,251
Just do it!

170
00:12:15,085 --> 00:12:17,283
Kiss her!

171
00:12:19,211 --> 00:12:23,584
My fantasy was always being Snow White.

172
00:12:30,425 --> 00:12:31,789
And now, finally,

173
00:12:32,367 --> 00:12:37,279
I felt like I became Snow White.

174
00:12:44,150 --> 00:12:47,348
Why would you put cherries in yogurt?

175
00:12:47,548 --> 00:12:50,239
You eat cherries by themselves!
Not with yogurt!

176
00:12:50,439 --> 00:12:52,681
You can just dip it if you want!

177
00:12:53,734 --> 00:12:54,900
Just dip it!

178
00:13:05,273 --> 00:13:07,292
I'm so sick of my stupid IBS.

179
00:13:08,650 --> 00:13:10,948
The person who left behind
their spare battery...

180
00:13:11,039 --> 00:13:13,217
...in the third-floor women's department,

181
00:13:13,308 --> 00:13:15,252
please come pick it up...

182
00:13:15,343 --> 00:13:16,702
- ...right away.
-What's that?

183
00:13:16,793 --> 00:13:18,306
Isn't that Mr Kim?

184
00:13:18,849 --> 00:13:20,650
Why is he making the announcement?

185
00:13:20,856 --> 00:13:22,558
Who says, "battery" like that?

186
00:13:22,649 --> 00:13:25,090
The PA girl suddenly took...

187
00:13:25,181 --> 00:13:27,625
...three months off.

188
00:13:27,716 --> 00:13:28,824
Why?

189
00:13:29,395 --> 00:13:30,887
She's getting married.

190
00:13:40,751 --> 00:13:42,351
Mr Kim. Here.

191
00:13:42,551 --> 00:13:44,661
What is it this time? You're scaring me.

192
00:13:44,861 --> 00:13:46,743
I thought you'd be extra tired today.

193
00:13:46,943 --> 00:13:49,506
You have your own job,
plus the announcements.

194
00:13:50,103 --> 00:13:52,292
What is it? Say what you want.

195
00:13:52,383 --> 00:13:55,253
It's what I've been
asking you for a while already.

196
00:13:55,344 --> 00:13:58,875
To give me a heads up
if the PA position opens up.

197
00:14:00,423 --> 00:14:04,476
You are quite the ambitious one,
aren't you?

198
00:14:05,065 --> 00:14:09,132
You must've been flustered
by the sudden resignation.

199
00:14:09,223 --> 00:14:12,865
People like me need to act
quickly in these situations.

200
00:14:13,080 --> 00:14:14,238
People like you?

201
00:14:14,925 --> 00:14:16,448
People on your side.

202
00:14:17,268 --> 00:14:18,265
Gosh.

203
00:14:20,564 --> 00:14:22,867
Mr Kim, you have the best eye.

204
00:14:23,176 --> 00:14:25,671
You should be a doctor.

205
00:14:26,316 --> 00:14:29,608
It was as if your own wife was dying.

206
00:14:30,919 --> 00:14:34,338
I learned the Heimlich maneuver
during training.

207
00:14:34,538 --> 00:14:37,740
Sure. I hope you'll work hard to...

208
00:14:38,618 --> 00:14:40,099
...on cleaning up too.

209
00:14:40,879 --> 00:14:43,569
Oh, my head.

210
00:14:47,021 --> 00:14:48,419
Why that...

211
00:14:48,510 --> 00:14:50,096
-Mr Kim.
-Yes?

212
00:14:50,953 --> 00:14:54,499
You were super cool.
A real knight in shining armor.

213
00:14:54,661 --> 00:14:57,510
It made me wish I had eaten that cherry.

214
00:14:59,522 --> 00:15:00,554
Sorry?

215
00:15:18,063 --> 00:15:20,375
It isn't that complicated.

216
00:15:20,575 --> 00:15:22,882
Just don't burp into the microphone.

217
00:15:23,226 --> 00:15:25,868
I'll hold interviews
no matter who may come.

218
00:15:25,959 --> 00:15:28,719
You can give it a shot then too.

219
00:15:28,919 --> 00:15:32,530
If you do well then,
you can make this seat yours.

220
00:15:32,621 --> 00:15:33,784
Really?

221
00:15:43,368 --> 00:15:44,650
How dare someone who served...

222
00:15:44,850 --> 00:15:47,038
...as a private lecture
an Army sharpshooter sergeant...

223
00:15:47,238 --> 00:15:49,348
...about respecting seniority? Why that...

224
00:15:49,439 --> 00:15:51,694
Seriously.

225
00:15:52,195 --> 00:15:54,298
Gosh, I can't take this anymore.

226
00:15:54,425 --> 00:15:58,877
Error Da.Aera

227
00:15:59,235 --> 00:16:01,730
You have such a bad timing, Aera.

228
00:16:02,539 --> 00:16:06,496
What do you want? Why are you calling me?

229
00:16:07,344 --> 00:16:09,812
How dare you order me to come?

230
00:16:10,012 --> 00:16:12,503
What? There's big news?

231
00:16:13,283 --> 00:16:15,997
So you're going to do
the in-house broadcasting today?

232
00:16:20,074 --> 00:16:22,268
Wait. But why did you ask me to come over?

233
00:16:22,468 --> 00:16:25,605
You should be here to
witness the historical moment.

234
00:16:25,805 --> 00:16:27,182
You also need to do something for me.

235
00:16:27,382 --> 00:16:29,184
My first broadcast starts at 3:30 p.m.

236
00:16:29,384 --> 00:16:31,317
It'll be my debut,
so please record it for me.

237
00:16:31,517 --> 00:16:34,301
You want me to record it? My goodness.

238
00:16:34,501 --> 00:16:36,200
You're making me do such ridiculous stuff.

239
00:16:36,400 --> 00:16:38,950
We only have 20 minutes
left until the live broadcast.

240
00:16:39,041 --> 00:16:41,909
I should hurry up and
wait beneath the speaker.

241
00:16:42,109 --> 00:16:45,722
My gosh, you really
know how to do a good job.

242
00:16:45,922 --> 00:16:46,961
Okay, let's go.

243
00:16:53,582 --> 00:16:56,855
Here's an announcement
for all our customers.

244
00:16:56,946 --> 00:17:01,312
Outdoor wear is on sale
on the eighth floor.

245
00:17:01,461 --> 00:17:05,218
If you're interested, please make a visit.

246
00:17:05,877 --> 00:17:08,766
I am Aera, and that's it
for the announcements.

247
00:17:11,330 --> 00:17:14,065
My gosh, she did a great job.

248
00:17:15,498 --> 00:17:17,485
She's as good as Baik Jiyeon.
Don't you think?

249
00:17:23,433 --> 00:17:25,219
My gosh, what should I do?

250
00:17:34,053 --> 00:17:38,055
Hey, she just said her name, right?

251
00:17:40,200 --> 00:17:43,112
Gosh, why would she say her name?

252
00:17:44,961 --> 00:17:47,086
Put on your gloves. You'll burn yourself.

253
00:17:47,286 --> 00:17:51,265
Outdoor wear is on sale
on the eighth floor.

254
00:17:51,356 --> 00:17:55,913
If you're interested,
please make a visit.

255
00:17:56,004 --> 00:17:59,218
I am Aera,
and that's it for the announcements.

256
00:18:02,655 --> 00:18:03,756
My gosh.

257
00:18:05,351 --> 00:18:06,691
What should I do?

258
00:18:06,891 --> 00:18:09,979
Why? Is there something wrong?

259
00:18:11,385 --> 00:18:13,357
It sounded perfect to me.

260
00:18:15,275 --> 00:18:16,384
What should I do?

261
00:18:17,549 --> 00:18:18,935
I'm...

262
00:18:20,070 --> 00:18:22,765
...so happy.

263
00:18:23,533 --> 00:18:24,984
I'm really happy.

264
00:18:27,261 --> 00:18:30,959
I guess people really need
to do what they love.

265
00:18:32,060 --> 00:18:33,758
Now that you've done what you love,

266
00:18:34,583 --> 00:18:35,869
are you that happy?

267
00:18:36,036 --> 00:18:37,221
I could die.

268
00:18:48,330 --> 00:18:50,150
An unknown box is being kept...

269
00:18:50,350 --> 00:18:52,129
...at the information desk
on the first floor.

